split
this
string
into
words
and
print
them
on
separate
lines
```
[/spoiler]

[spoiler title='Hint' collapse_link='true']
Iterate over the characters in the string. Keep track of the longest word you've encountered so far.
[/spoiler]

[spoiler title='Solution' collapse_link='true']
```swift
var problem = "split this string into words and print them on separate lines"

var word = ""

for character in problem.characters {
    if character == " " {
        print(word)
        word = ""
    } else {
        word += "\(character)"
    }
}

// don't forget the last word
print(word)

// split
// this
// string
// into
// words
// and
// print
// them
// on
// separate
// lines
```
